what is a good darker color to paint a room that promotes relaxation and doesn't feel crowded or small i'm repainting my room a bedroom blues greens or taupes are relaxing not sure what your definition of dark is but too dark would not be too relaxing to me i would go about midway down the paint wheel to find a color you like as mentioned above sage is nice so is a lovely shade of medium glass blue or a grayish taupe though be careful with the latter as it could end up looking depressing if the rest of the room is dark as well skies the limit when it comes to paint colors try looking on line at benjaminmoore com for ideas Color Color theory Blue Microsoft Paint Drawing Sunglasses Glass Wassily Kandinsky Art Super Chief Eye color Light-emitting diode Red RGB color model Rei Ayanami Wood Atchison, Topeka and Santa Fe Railway Coffee The Brady Bunch Mario series enemies Georges-Pierre Seurat Mid-levels The Wall Minor characters from The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy Heavy metal music Care Bears Television Dundas Square The Legend of Zelda: A Link to the Past British Rail Class 50 Liquid crystal display Marc Chagall Friends Johnny the Homicidal Maniac Yu-Gi-Oh! Trading Card Game Impressionism British Rail Class 86 Chatsworth House Link (Legend of Zelda) Pennsylvania Railroad Scenes from a Memory Color blindness Sky Mona Lisa Fancy rat Garnet Blood on the Tracks Dragon Booster Diamond enhancement Black (people) Black Disneyland Sin City Characters in the Smurfs Frankie Laine Castlevania: Harmony of Dissonance Sage James McNeill Whistler Rainbow Brite Myofibril Scrubs Pysanka Upholstery __douard Manet Qualia Vitreous enamel Chao (Sonic the Hedgehog) Wallpaper group Nintendo 64 Primary color Green Union Pacific Railroad Planet Waves Ages of Myst Aes Sedai Iris (anatomy) Dualism (philosophy of mind) Purple My Little Pony Bubble Bobble Professional wrestling slang Chromotherapy New York City Subway nomenclature Insomnia The Wizard of Oz (1939 film) BNSF Railway Lighting Se